This project will consist of the following:
  1. A playable version of Battleship
      1a. Playable against an AI or a human opponent.
        a1. AI will have one dificutly setting that will randomly guess ship positions until it strikes, then guesses within 1 square of hit.
        a2. Players will input a simple pin to prevent opponent from seeing their board when it's passed to them, this will be assigned at
            the ship positioning stage.
      1b. Using SDL to create the GUI this project will have simple graphics displaying the current player's ships and where they
          have shot on the opponents board.
      1c. It will use the Milton Bradley rule-set and ship count.
  2. A main menu and save states.
      2a. A main GUI menu to pick the opponent from.
      2b. Save states to resume games at a later date.
        b1. Save states will store current board, including fired shots and pins.
  3. ???
